HEADWORD: holdover
<hw>holdover</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>Any person or thing remaining from
a previous period of use, tenure, etc;</def>
<specif>Specifically:</specif> <def>an official who remains in office
after his term.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> hangover.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Holdup</ent>⟦br⟧
